[30;1m1656 | [0m[35m#[0m
[30;1m1657 | [0m[35m# In Unix terms top of stack is argument transfer area for arguments[0m
[30;1m1658 | [0m[35m# which could not be accommodated in registers. Or in other words 7th[0m
[30;1m1659 | [0m[35m# [integer] argument resides at 8(%rsp) upon function entry point.[0m
[30;1m1660 | [0m[35m# 128 bytes above %rsp constitute a "red zone" which is not touched[0m
